Relational Behaviors 
Negotiations 
Negotiations are dynamic situations that require adaptation and immediate responses for 
those involved. Negotiations are, in essence, social problem solving situations. Accordingly, how 
proficient individuals are at social-problem solving (e.g., building rapport; perspective taking) 
predicts how well they act as negotiators (see Bazerman, Curhan, Moore, & Valley, 2000). These 
social-oriented tasks depend on executive functions (Wardlow, 2013), but little attention has 
